156
00:11:15,432 --> 00:11:17,635
The ocean sunfish isn't bad.

157
00:11:18,799 --> 00:11:20,371
What?

158
00:11:22,399 --> 00:11:26,232
I think ocean sunfish will surely be popular.

159
00:11:28,099 --> 00:11:31,919
But I heard that ocean sunfish die easily.

160
00:11:31,919 --> 00:11:34,099
That's a rumor.

161
00:11:35,265 --> 00:11:37,299
Is that so?

162
00:11:37,999 --> 00:11:40,899
The ocean sunfish is not that fragile.

163
00:11:44,265 --> 00:11:48,399
I want to see the ocean sunfish that you like, Shioya-san.

164
00:11:53,565 --> 00:11:55,132
The ocean sunfish.

165
00:11:55,132 --> 00:11:56,407
Actually...

166
00:11:56,407 --> 00:11:58,332
It's swift.

167
00:11:58,332 --> 00:12:05,365
I need to find out what Shioya-san... really thinks of me.

168
00:12:08,799 --> 00:12:10,632
Is something wrong?

169
00:12:11,165 --> 00:12:14,099
No, nothing.

170
00:12:15,965 --> 00:12:17,799
Let's go.

171
00:12:17,799 --> 00:12:19,735
Okay.

172
00:12:21,865 --> 00:12:25,931
But I fear it may destroy our current relationship.

173
00:12:26,799 --> 00:12:29,199
So I can't ask anything.

174
00:12:31,932 --> 00:12:39,007
I didn't expect that after the aquarium, we would eat seafood.

175
00:12:39,765 --> 00:12:44,579
Fish are ideal to view and to eat.

176
00:12:47,519 --> 00:12:51,799
I've learned a lot today,

177
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:54,403
many things I didn't know about you.

178
00:12:55,532 --> 00:12:57,165
Is that so?

179
00:12:58,299 --> 00:13:00,515
But in the end,

180
00:13:01,499 --> 00:13:04,907
I didn't ask the most important question.

181
00:13:07,699 --> 00:13:10,599
I'm heading that way.

182
00:13:14,032 --> 00:13:15,799
Be careful.

183
00:13:16,599 --> 00:13:18,223
All right.

184
00:13:32,665 --> 00:13:34,523
Well,

185
00:13:41,899 --> 00:13:46,299
can we chat for a bit more?

186
00:13:50,632 --> 00:13:54,032
So what did you want to talk about?

187
00:13:54,032 --> 00:13:56,399
Well…

188
00:13:58,865 --> 00:14:03,765
What exactly am I to you, Shioya-san?

189
00:14:06,111 --> 00:14:07,165
What?

190
00:14:07,165 --> 00:14:11,232
How should I put it?

191
00:14:11,932 --> 00:14:15,747
I'm wondering, what stage are we?

192
00:14:23,399 --> 00:14:29,832
I think we're… dating.

193
00:14:29,832 --> 00:14:31,265
What?

194
00:14:33,230 --> 00:14:35,232
Da… dating?

195
00:14:35,232 --> 00:14:38,165
You and me?

196
00:14:38,165 --> 00:14:42,595
If I misunderstood, I apologize.

197
00:14:43,532 --> 00:14:45,071
I…

198
00:14:46,232 --> 00:14:51,363
I don't have much experience dating girls.

199
00:14:52,990 --> 00:14:55,527
Wait… But…

200
00:14:55,527 --> 00:14:56,410
I…

201
00:14:56,410 --> 00:14:57,860
That morning,

202
00:14:57,860 --> 00:15:00,799
- when I told you I liked you,
- I like you.

203
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:06,307
you didn't react, and…

204
00:15:07,930 --> 00:15:10,832
Oh, that's because…

205
00:15:13,230 --> 00:15:16,515
Luckily, the alarm rang.

206
00:15:18,999 --> 00:15:22,275
I almost wanted to take her again.

207
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:29,965
That night, you said you liked me

208
00:15:30,865 --> 00:15:35,299
so I thought we started dating then.

209
00:15:39,099 --> 00:15:40,332
Pardon me,

210
00:15:40,332 --> 00:15:45,565
I was very drunk that night.

211
00:15:49,430 --> 00:15:52,265
To put your mind at ease,

212
00:15:52,265 --> 00:15:56,459
I'll say it seriously again.

213
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:10,220
Sato-san,

214
00:16:10,220 --> 00:16:15,600
please... date me.

215
00:16:30,430 --> 00:16:34,851
Excuse me, I'm thrilled.

216
00:16:53,265 --> 00:16:55,223
Nice to meet you,

217
00:16:57,132 --> 00:16:59,847
"My Boyfriend."

218
00:17:19,030 --> 00:17:20,932
Nice to meet you, too.

219
00:17:23,132 --> 00:17:27,995
I won't make you that anxious again.

220
00:17:32,465 --> 00:17:35,975
What did you just say?

221
00:17:49,665 --> 00:17:52,132
Please… please wait a moment.

222
00:17:52,132 --> 00:17:55,332
I'm not mentally prepared yet.

223
00:17:55,332 --> 00:17:57,032
I can't wait.

224
00:18:05,899 --> 00:18:08,295
I can't wait now.

225
00:18:31,165 --> 00:18:36,099
When you're so cute,

226
00:18:36,099 --> 00:18:38,299
I won't be able to control myself.

227
00:18:50,143 --> 00:18:52,732
Shioya-san.

228
00:18:52,732 --> 00:18:54,665
What's wrong?

229
00:18:54,665 --> 00:18:57,511
Shioya-san, you are…

230
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:02,027
actually very passionate.

231
00:19:07,932 --> 00:19:09,687
I guess.

232
00:19:17,371 --> 00:19:20,432
